From 643cceec6cfed1b2402ede45800debc27dfd8bc9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Craig Hart <craig.d.hart3@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 19:13:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix mobile layout: unified CSS, consistent scroll containers,
 compact nav
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Rewrote mobile.css: removed triple overflow lock, fixed aggressive
  44px min-height on ALL buttons/links (now only primary interactives),
  added btn-compact opt-out class for inline buttons
- Rewrote globals.css: removed light theme body (bg-gray-50 → bg-gray-900),
  removed duplicate tap target rules, updated component classes to dark theme
- Fixed _app.js loading spinner to use dark theme
- Dashboard: use page-content class, add border-b to header, shrink
  CalorieRing SVG from 160px to 128px for mobile
- BottomNav: add backdrop-blur, reduce icon size (2xl→xl), tighten padding
  (py-3→py-2, min-h-56→52), smaller labels (xs→[10px])
- Standardised all pages to pb-24 bottom padding for nav clearance:
  meals (was pb-40), food (was pb-36), log-dose (had none),
  configure-peptides (had none), peptides (had none), peptides/[id] (had none)

All 19 pages now use shared BottomNav + page-content scroll pattern.
Build passes cleanly.
